description:
Career

Jeff Lindsay is best known as the author of the Dexter series of novels, the protagonist of which is a sociopathic serial killer and blood spatter analyst for Miami Police Department. His works have been adapted into a successful television series starring Michael C Hall and Jennifer Carpenter. Lindsay is a creative consultant on the show, and has personally approved many of the crucial character and plot differences between the novels and the series, even having a brief on screen cameo on the show.

Dexter has also been adapted to into a comic book series by Marvel.

Novels

  • Darkly Dreaming Dexter (2004)
  • Dearly Devoted Dexter (2005)
  • Dexter in the Dark (2007)
  • Dexter by Design (2009)
  • Dexter Is Delicious (2010)
  • Double Dexter (2011)
  • Dexter's Final Cut (2013, TBR)
name: Jeff Lindsay

description:
Career

David Schulner is a writer for both TV and comics. His first comic book was Clone, published out of Skybound.

He is also known for writing on television shows such as Desperate Housewives, Trauma and The Event. More recently he created his first TV series, Do No Harm, which was cancelled after 2 episodes.
name: David Schulner
